# Wakanda Forever

## {Intro @unplugged}

Help Shuri, Okoye, and Riri Williams (Ironheart) escape Namor.

Design a game in MakeCode Arcade, creating sprites for Shuri, Okoye, Ironheart, and Namor.

## {Step 2}

First, let's set a scene background for Wakanda by using the code block that will place an
image for the background.

---

- :tree: From the ``||scene:Scene||`` category, grab <br/>
``||scene:set background image to [ ]||`` with the "Wakanda" image<br/>
and snap it into the empty <br/>
``||loops:on start||`` <br/>
container already in the workspace.

```blocks
scene.setBackgroundImage(assets.image`wakanda`)
```

## {Step 3}


**Introduce Shuri to the game as a new sprite**

---

- :paper plane: From ``||sprites:Sprites||``, drag   
``||variables:set [mySprite] to sprite [ ] of kind [Player]||``  
into **the end** of the  
``||loops:on start||`` container.

- :paint brush: Click the grey box in the new block to open the **image editor**.

_ðŸ’¡ Switch over to **My Assets** to choose the image for Shuri._

```blocks
scene.setBackgroundImage(assets.image`wakanda`)
let Shuri = sprites.create(assets.image`shuri`, SpriteKind.Player)
```

## {Step 3.5}


**Allow Shuri to move inside the screen boundary**

We need to give Shuri the ability move around when the controller buttons are pressed.

---

- :paper plane: From ``||controller:Controller||``, grab a <br/>
``||controller:move Shuri with buttons||`` <br/>
block and set the sprite variable to **Shuri**.<br/>

---

Oh yes, make sure Shuri stays on the screen by turning on a sprite **flag**.

---

- :paper plane: In ``||sprites:Sprites||``, get the <br/>
``||sprites:set stay in screen||`` <br/>
block and move the green toggle switch to **ON**.<br/>

```blocks   
scene.setBackgroundImage(assets.image`wakanda`)
let Shuri = sprites.create(assets.image`shuri`, SpriteKind.Player)
controller.moveSprite(Shuri)
Shuri.setStayInScreen(true)
```

## {Step 4}


**Add Namor to the game as Shuri's enemy**

---

- :paper plane: From ``||sprites:Sprites||``, drag   
``||variables:set [mySprite] to sprite [ ] of kind [Player]||``  
into **the end** of the  
``||loops:on start||`` container.

- :paint brush: Click the grey box in the new block to open the **image editor**.

_ðŸ’¡ Switch over to **My Assets** to choose the image for Namor._

```blocks
scene.setBackgroundImage(assets.image`wakanda`)
let Shuri = sprites.create(assets.image`shuri`, SpriteKind.Player)
controller.moveSprite(Shuri)
Shuri.setStayInScreen(true)
let Namor = sprites.create(assets.image`namor`, SpriteKind.Enemy)
```

## {Step 4.5}


Namor will start in the upper corner of the screen and chase Shuri all around the screen.

---

- :paper plane: In ``||sprites:Sprites||``, pull out the <br/>
``||sprites:set Namor follow Shuri with speed 30||``.

- :paper plane: Set Namor's initial position with the ``||sprites:set Namor position to x 148 y 2||`` block.

```blocks
scene.setBackgroundImage(assets.image`wakanda`)
let Shuri = sprites.create(assets.image`shuri`, SpriteKind.Player)
controller.moveSprite(Shuri)
Shuri.setStayInScreen(true)
let Namor = sprites.create(assets.image`namor`, SpriteKind.Enemy)
Namor.follow(Shuri, 30)
Namor.setPosition(148, 2)
```

## {Step 5}

**Namor attacks Shuri, she loses life points!**

If Namor reaches Shuri, she will lose a life point. Namor will thrn go back to the corner to start chasing again. The game detects when Namor gets to Shuri by using a sprite overlap event block.

---

- :paper plane: In ``||sprites:Sprites||``, grab a <br/>
``||sprites:on sprite of kind Player overlaps other sprite of kind Enemy||`` block.<br/>
Put it somewhere out on the Workspace.

- :paper plane: To subtract a life from Shuri, go into ``||info:Info||`` and get the ``||info:change life by -1||``.<br/>
Put this in to the overlap event block.<br/>

- :paper plane: Send Namor back to the corner of the screen by placing<br/>
the ``||sprites:set Namor position to x 148 y 2||`` block into the overlap event.

```blocks
sprites.onOverlap(SpriteKind.Player, SpriteKind.Enemy, function (sprite, otherSprite) {
    info.changeLifeBy(-1)
    otherSprite.setPosition(148, 2)
})
```

## {Step 6}

**Give Shuri some lives**

Shuri needs some life points to start with!

---

- :paper plane: Get an  ``||info:set life to 2||`` from ``||info:Info||``<br/>
and put it at the beginning of ``||loops:on start||``.

```blocks
info.setLife(2)
scene.setBackgroundImage(assets.image`wakanda`)
let Shuri = sprites.create(assets.image`shuri`, SpriteKind.Player)
controller.moveSprite(Shuri)
Shuri.setStayInScreen(true)
let Namor = sprites.create(assets.image`namor`, SpriteKind.Enemy)
Namor.follow(Shuri, 30)
Namor.setPosition(148, 2)
```

## {Step 7}

**Bring in the guards!**

Both Riri and Okoye join the game to help Shuri and guard her from Namor's attacks.

- :paper plane: From ``||sprites:Sprites||``, drag out 
``||variables:set [Riri] to sprite [ ] of kind [Guard]||``<br/>
and  ``||variables:set [Okoye] to sprite [ ] of kind [Guard]||``<br/> 
into **the end** of the  
``||loops:on start||`` container.

- :paint brush: Click the grey box in the block for **Riri** to open the **image editor**.

_ðŸ’¡ Switch over to **My Assets** to choose the image for Riri._

- :paint brush: Click the grey box in the block for **Okoye** to open the **image editor**.

_ðŸ’¡ Switch over to **My Assets** to choose the image for Okoye._


```blocks
namespace SpriteKind {
    export const Guard = SpriteKind.create()
}
info.setLife(2)
scene.setBackgroundImage(assets.image`wakanda`)
let Shuri = sprites.create(assets.image`shuri`, SpriteKind.Player)
controller.moveSprite(Shuri)
Shuri.setStayInScreen(true)
let Namor = sprites.create(assets.image`namor`, SpriteKind.Enemy)
Namor.follow(Shuri, 30)
Namor.setPosition(148, 2)
let Riri = sprites.create(assets.image`riri`, SpriteKind.Guard)
let Okoye = sprites.create(assets.image`okoye`, SpriteKind.Guard)
```

## {Step 7.5}

**Make the guards move**

---

- :paper plane: Just below the sprite block for **Riri**,  put in the ``||controller:move Riri with buttons vx 34 vy -53||`` block.

- :paper plane: Just below the sprite block for **Okoye**,  put in the ``||controller:move Okoye with buttons vx -68 vy -58||`` block.

```blocks
namespace SpriteKind {
    export const Guard = SpriteKind.create()
}
info.setLife(2)
scene.setBackgroundImage(assets.image`wakanda`)
let Shuri = sprites.create(assets.image`shuri`, SpriteKind.Player)
controller.moveSprite(Shuri)
Shuri.setStayInScreen(true)
let Namor = sprites.create(assets.image`namor`, SpriteKind.Enemy)
Namor.follow(Shuri, 30)
Namor.setPosition(148, 2)
let Riri = sprites.create(assets.image`riri`, SpriteKind.Guard)
controller.moveSprite(Riri, 34, -53)
let Okoye = sprites.create(assets.image`okoye`, SpriteKind.Guard)
controller.moveSprite(Okoye, -68, -58)
```

## {Step 8}

If one the guards can catch Namor, add a point to the game score. Namor should go back to his corner and start to attack again after being caught.

---

- :paper plane: In ``||sprites:Sprites||``, grab a <br/>
``||sprites:on sprite of kind Guard overlaps other sprite of kind Enemy||`` block.<br/>
Put it somewhere out on the Workspace.

- :paper plane: Add a point to the game score with a ``||info:change score by 1||`` inside this new event.<br/>
Put this in to the overlap event block.<br/>

- :paper plane: Send Namor back to the corner of the screen by placing<br/>
the ``||sprites:set Namor position to x 148 y 2||`` block into the overlap event.

```blocks
sprites.onOverlap(SpriteKind.Guard, SpriteKind.Enemy, function (sprite, otherSprite) {
    info.changeScoreBy(1)
    otherSprite.setPosition(148, 2)
})
```

## {Step 9}

Well, let's decide when Shuri, with the help Riri and Okoye, will win against Namor's attacks. If the game score reaches **20** then Shuri wins!

---

- :paper plane: In ``||info:Info||``, grab an ``||info:on score 20||`` event block.<br/>
Put it somewhere out on the Workspace.

- :paper plane: Over in ``||sprites:Sprites||``, get the ``||sprites:destroy Namor||`` block<br/>
and put it in the event to destory Namor.

- :paper plane: From in ``||game:Game||``, grab a ``||game:game over true||`` block and put it in at the end of the event. This will end the game.

```blocks
info.onScore(20, function () {
    Namor.destroy()
    scene.setBackgroundImage(assets.image`boston-bridge`)
    game.over(true)
})
```

## {Step 9.5}

**Celebrate the victory!**


Make defeating Namor a much more dramatic event. Add some effects and messages to celebrate the win!.

---

- :tree: From the ``||scene:Scene||`` category, grab <br/>
``||scene:set background image to [ ]||`` with the image of the Boston Bridge. <br/>
Pull it into the ``||info:on score 20||`` block after ``||sprites:destroy Namor||``.

- :paper plane: Get a ``||scene:start screen confetti effect||`` a place it after the background image block.

- :paper plane: Next, display a message with a ``||game:show long text "We are safe!" top||`` block.

- :paper plane: make Shuri shout "WAKANDA FOREVER" next to her sprite.<br/>
Use the ``||sprites:Shuri say "WAKANDA FOREVER" for 5000 ms||`` block.

```blocks
info.onScore(20, function () {
    Namor.destroy()
    scene.setBackgroundImage(assets.image`boston-bridge`)
    effects.confetti.startScreenEffect()
    game.showLongText("We are safe!", DialogLayout.Top)
    Shuri.sayText("WAKANDA FOREVER!", 5000, false)
    game.over(true)
})
```

## {Step 10}


**Instructions please!**

Now that the game is mostly complete, let's give the player some brief instructions on how to play.

---

- :paper plane: Find the  ``||game:show long text "Help Shuri, Okoye and Riri escape Namor." full screen||`` block. Put it in the ``||loops.on start||`` after the ``||info:set life 2||``.

- :paper plane: Right after that first instruction, put in the ``||game:show long text "When game begins, press the ARROW KEYS to move Shuri, Okoye and Riri." full screen||`` block.

- :paper plane: Now, after the second instruction, put in ``||game:show long text ""Earn 20 points to win and to stay alive you must keep your heart(s)." full screen||``.

```blocks
namespace SpriteKind {
    export const Guard = SpriteKind.create()
}
info.setLife(2)
scene.setBackgroundImage(assets.image`wakanda`)
let Shuri = sprites.create(assets.image`shuri`, SpriteKind.Player)
controller.moveSprite(Shuri)
Shuri.setStayInScreen(true)
let Namor = sprites.create(assets.image`namor`, SpriteKind.Enemy)
Namor.follow(Shuri, 30)
Namor.setPosition(148, 2)
let Riri = sprites.create(assets.image`riri`, SpriteKind.Guard)
controller.moveSprite(Riri, 34, -53)
let Okoye = sprites.create(assets.image`okoye`, SpriteKind.Guard)
controller.moveSprite(Okoye, -68, -58)
game.showLongText("Help Shuri, Okoye and Riri escape Namor.       (Press the \"A\" button to go to the next screen.)", DialogLayout.Full)
game.showLongText("When game begins, press the ARROW KEYS to move Shuri, Okoye and Riri. If Namor catches you, you will lose points! ", DialogLayout.Full)
game.showLongText("Earn 20 points to win and to stay alive you must keep your heart(s).", DialogLayout.Full)
```
